'''Reina March''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] criminal [[Homeworld/Legends|from]] the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] who was the leader and [[Lieutenant/Legends|head lieutenant]] of the anarchist organization [[Edge-9]]. In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], she visited the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]] on her homeworld with the [[Con artist/Legends|con artist]] [[Dannl Faytonni/Legends|Dannl Faytonni]] and the woman [[Whimper Save]] at the same time as the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] [[Zam Wesell/Legends|Zam Wesell]] and [[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]]. She again visited the club with Faytonni and Save when the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] [[Plot to assassinate Senator Amidala/Legends|entered]] looking for Wesell.  

==Biography==
[[File:FaytonniReinaWhimper-AOTC.png|thumb|right|350px|March turned to stare at the disarming of Zam Wesell.]]
Reina March was a young<ref name="CoruscantCore" /> [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] criminal who [[Coruscanti/Legends|hailed]] [[Homeworld/Legends|from]]<ref name="DB" /> the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="CoruscantCore">''[[Coruscant and the Core Worlds]]''</ref> [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]].<ref name="DB" /> March was the leader and [[Lieutenant/Legends|head lieutenant]] of the anarchist organization [[Edge-9]]<ref name="CoruscantCore" /> during the last [[Standard decade/Legends|decades]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].<ref name="DB" /> Her organization called for the dismantling of Coruscant's government and the abolition of its noble upper class. Although the groups motives seemed noble, March and other members of the group turned to violence to get their message across.<ref name="CoruscantCore" /> She occasionally accompanied the<ref name="DB" /> [[Con artist/Legends|con artist]]<ref name="db">{{DB|character|lieutenantfaytonni|Faytonni, Lieutenant Dannl}}</ref> [[Dannl Faytonni/Legends|Dannl Faytonni]] in the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]],<ref name="DB" /> a [[Nightclub/Legends|nightclub]] and [[Gambling/Legends|gambling]] hall in the [[Uscru Entertainment District/Legends|Uscru Entertainment District]] of Coruscant.<ref name="CSWE2">{{CSWECite|II|431|Outlander Club}}</ref> 

In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="NEC Note">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of {{Film|II}} to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]]. The scene from ''[[Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter]]'' in which [[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]] is in the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]] takes place immediately before the film, meaning it must be set in that [[Standard year/Legends|year]].</ref> March visited the club while [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] [[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]] and [[Zam Wesell/Legends|Zam Wesell]] met there. She was accompanied by Faytonni and<ref name="Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter">''[[Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter]]''</ref> the woman [[Whimper Save]].<ref name="Save">{{DB|character|whimpersave|Save, Whimper}}</ref> Shortly after,<ref name="NEC Note" /> March, Faytonni, and Save visited the club the [[Local day/Legends|night]] of Wesell's [[Plot to assassinate Senator Amidala/Legends|attempted assassination]] of [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]]. As the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] entered to club trying to find the bounty hunter, the trio talked with each other at the bar. When Kenobi made his way to the bar, March talked with a Human who joined their group before they departed as she waved at them. Not long after, Kenobi disarmed Wesell at the bar, causing March and her companions to look at the altercation. Skywalker told the clubgoers to go back to their drinks and March turned her attention back to her group.<ref name="AoTC" />

==Personality and traits==
March wore a perpetual scowl and had [[Color/Legends|brown]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]] kept short,<ref name="CoruscantCore" /> light skin, and dark colored [[Eye/Legends|eyes]].<ref name="DB" /> With the fervor of youth, she believed in the cause of Edge-9 and used violence to get the groups message across.<ref name="CoruscantCore" />

==Skills and abilities==
March was a martial artist<ref name="CoruscantCore" /> who was known<ref name="DB" /> for her excellent hand-to-hand fighting skils. She was proficient in the use of [[Blaster pistol/Legends|blaster pistols]], [[Vibro-weapon/Legends|vibro-weapons]], and simple weapons. March was also skilled in demolitions, disguising, and gathering information. The anarchist was knowledgeable on her homeworld and its politics.<ref name="CoruscantCore" /> She was able to [[Language/Legends|speak]], read, and write in [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Basic]].<ref name="CoruscantCore" />

==Equipment==
March possessed an encoded [[Comlink/Legends|comlink]], a [[frequency jammer]], a [[Vibroblade/Legends|vibroblade]], and a [[Heavy blaster pistol/Legends|heavy blaster pistol]]. March favored inconspicuous black clothing<ref name="CoruscantCore" /> to blend into a crowd with.<ref name="DB" /> During her two visits to the Outlander Club<ref name="Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter" /><ref name="AoTC" /> in 22 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|BBY]],<ref name="NEC Note" /> she wore a dark top paired with dark gloves.<ref name="AoTC" />

==Behind the scenes==
===Filming and first appearances===
[[File:Faytonni_ep2dvd.jpg|thumb|right|300px|The uncredited extra playing March on set.]]
Reina March was first mentioned in ''[[Coruscant and the Core Worlds]]'', a [[2003]] sourcebook for the [[Star Wars Roleplaying Game]] published by [[Wizards of the Coast]].<ref name="CoruscantCore" /> In ''[[Dressing a Galaxy: The Costumes of Star Wars]]'', a [[2005]] book written by costume designer [[Trisha Biggar]],<ref name="DaG">''[[Dressing a Galaxy: The Costumes of Star Wars]]''</ref> March was identified as a character appearing in the [[prequel trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']],<ref name="AoTC" /> which released on [[May 16]], [[2002]].<ref name="Year">''[[Star Wars Year by Year: A Visual Chronicle]]''</ref> 

The Outlander Club scenes, where the character was portrayed by an uncredited extra, were shot at [[Fox Studios, Sydney]] on [[July 17]], [[2000]].<ref name="Mythmaking">''[[Mythmaking: Behind the Scenes of Attack of the Clones]]''</ref> March was first shown with the release of the trailer for Episode II<ref name="Trailer">{{SW|url=video/episode-ii-trailer-clone-war|text=Attack of the Clones Trailer: Clone War &#124; Video}}</ref> on [[March 10]], 2002.<ref name="TrailerRelease2">{{WebCite|url=https://ew.com/article/2002/03/04/sneak-peek-next-episode-ii-trailer|text=A sneak peek at the next <nowiki>''</nowiki>Episode II<nowiki>''</nowiki> trailer|author=Brown, Scott|date=2002-03-04|work=[[Wikipedia:Entertainment Weekly|''Entertainment Weekly'']]|quote=On March 10, the latest two-and-a-half-minute tease for "Attack of the Clones" will hit screens|archivedate=20231127115801}}</ref> The character then made her first appearances in illustrations in the upcoming films' [[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones Movie Storybook|storybook]], written by [[Jane Mason]] and [[Sarah Hines Stephens]];<ref name="Storybook">''[[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones Movie Storybook]]''</ref> its young readers book [[Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter|''Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter'']], written by [[Eric Arnold]] and illustrated by [[Valerie Reckert]];<ref name="Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter2">''[[Jango Fett: Bounty Hunter]]''</ref> and the film's [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones (junior novelization)|junior novelization]], written by [[Patricia C. Wrede]]. All three books were released on [[April 23]], 2002,<ref name="BHRelease">{{SWArchive|url=eu/lit/young/news20020225.html|text=Book Preview: Episode II Children's Books}}</ref> and the images of her in the books were all taken from the then-upcoming film.<ref name="aotc">{{Film|II}}</ref>

===Roleplaying scenario===
In ''Coruscant and the Core Worlds'', March is featured in the roleplaying adventure "Panic in the Plaza." In the adventure, set during the time of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] on Coruscant, March and other Edge-9 members plan to sabotage the [[Galactic Fair|Imperial Fair]] on the [[Glitannai Esplanade]] by commandeering an armored vehicle and steering it into crowds of people. The parade hijacking serves as a cover for March's storming of the [[Imperial Palace/Legends|Imperial Palace's]] observation balcony, where she would [[Death/Legends|kill]] the high-level politicians there. The heroes playing the adventure may be hired to stop the anarchist attack or be participating in the celebration.<ref name="CoruscantCore" /> 

